# TypeScript Style

- Keep TypeScript strict and avoid `any`.
- Prefer explicit interfaces and descriptive names over comments.
- Do not add JSDoc comments.
- Keep code readable before optimizing for brevity.
- Use existing package patterns before adding new abstractions.
- Keep shared domain contracts in `@meicontrol/types`.
- Keep reusable React components in `@meicontrol/ui`.
- Preserve the formatting style of the package being edited.

For cross-package changes, validate with:

```bash
pnpm lint
pnpm build
```
